A 'Euphorbia hypericifolia' is a species of flowering plant that belongs to the Euphorbia family. 
It is commonly known as the St. John's Wort Spurge and is native to the Americas. 
The plant has a bushy growth habit and reaches a height of up to 24 inches. 
The leaves are small and dark green with a smooth texture. 
The flowers are yellow-green in color, with five petals, and appear in clusters on top of the stem. 
They bloom from late spring through early fall. 
'  Euphorbia hypericifolia' is commonly used as an ornamental plant in gardens, parks or as a potted plant indoors.
